						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near a well in the shephered's street.</p>						

						<p>This is dated only in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Krōdhi Nija Āshāḍha śu. 15, Friday.</hi> However, on the basis of palaeography, it may be assigned to the 18th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It states that the step-well was constructed by the merchants <hi rend="italic">(Nagarasvāmis).</hi> It also mentions Nagarēśvaradēva.</p>						

						</summary>
